EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO PUBLIC UTILITIES AND CARRIERS - REGULATORY POWERS OF
ADMINISTRATION
***
1 This act would provide that any rate increase with respect to electric distribution companies
2 would be no greater than the increase in the Consumer Price Index or five and one-half percent
3 (5.5%), whichever is greater, unless there is approval of a higher rate by the general assembly.
4 This act would take effect upon passage.
